        <div class="container faq-page" style="margin-top: 100px; color: #fff;">
            <div class="faq-header">Frequently Asked Questions</div>
            <p class="mt-2 p-2">
                This FAQ (Frequently Asked Questions) section is designed to provide quick and easy answers to common inquiries. Whether you're seeking information about our services, policies, or troubleshooting tips, this guide aims to address your most pressing questions.
                We’ve organized the FAQs into categories to help you find the answers you need as efficiently as possible. If your question isn’t covered here or if you need further assistance, feel free to reach out to our support team for personalized help.
            </p>
            <hr>
            <div class="faq-content">
                <div class="faq-question">
                    <input id="q1" type="checkbox" class="panel">
                    <div class="plus">+</div>
                    <label for="q1" class="panel-title">What is a cryptocurrency exchange?</label>
                    <div class="panel-content">A cryptocurrency exchange is a digital platform that allows users to buy, sell, and trade cryptocurrencies like Bitcoin, Ethereum, and others. It acts as a marketplace for crypto transactions, often offering additional features like wallets, analytics, and trading tools.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-question">
                    <input id="q2" type="checkbox" class="panel">
                    <div class="plus">+</div>
                    <label for="q2" class="panel-title">How do I create an account?</label>
                    <div class="panel-content">To create an account, visit the exchange website or app, click on "Sign Up," and fill in the required information. You may also need to verify your identity through a Know Your Customer (KYC) process.</div>
                </div>    
                <div class="faq-question">
                    <input id="q3" type="checkbox" class="panel">
                    <div class="plus">+</div>
                    <label for="q3" class="panel-title">What is KYC, and why is it required?</label>
                    <div class="panel-content">KYC (Know Your Customer) is a verification process that confirms your identity. It’s required by law to prevent fraud, money laundering, and other illicit activities. KYC involves providing personal details and uploading ID documents.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-question">
                    <input id="q4" type="checkbox" class="panel">
                    <div class="plus">+</div>
                    <label for="q4" class="panel-title">Are cryptocurrency exchanges safe?</label>
                    <div class="panel-content">Reputable exchanges use advanced security measures like encryption, two-factor authentication (2FA), and cold wallets to protect users. However, users should also secure their accounts by using strong passwords and enabling 2FA.</div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-question">
                    <input id="q5" type="checkbox" class="panel">
                    <div class="plus">+</div>
                    <label for="q5" class="panel-title">What fees does the exchange charge?</label>
                    <div class="panel-content">
                        Most exchanges charge:
                        Trading fees: A small percentage per transaction.
                        Withdrawal fees: Fees for transferring crypto to external wallets.
                        Deposit fees: Rare but may apply for certain payment methods.
                        Fees vary by platform and transaction type, so check the fee schedule before trading.
                    </div>
